    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                <date>August 28th 5610</date>
            </p>
            <p>To Messrs <addressee>C Lichten</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>E Bamberger</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>L. Silberman</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Louisville</placeName>.</p>
            <p>Gentlemen</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours of <date>August 15</date> postmarked the <date>23</date> came
                to hand this mor-<lb/>ning, and it appears at first sight singular that 8 days
                should have<lb/> passed between it being written and markedâ€”for the second
                place<lb/> I have no personal knowledge whatsoever of the <persName>Rev. H. C.
                    Henry</persName><lb/> never having met him in my life, and not having examined
                any<lb/> of his writings or credentials. But <persName>Rev. Dr. Raphall</persName>
                of the <placeName>Elm<lb/> Street</placeName> Synagogue <placeName>New
                    York</placeName> has some personal knowledge of<lb/> him, as also my friend
                    <persName>Rev. J. K. Gutheim</persName> late of
                    <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName><lb/> whose place <persName>Mr.
                    <add>?</add></persName> obtained last <add>?</add>. I have no<lb/> doubt that if
                your election is postponed for two or three months<lb/>
                <add>?</add> could correspond with these two ministers &amp; <persName>Mr.<lb/>
                    Henry's</persName> late congregation in <placeName>London</placeName>, you will
                obtain all<lb/> the information necessary and which <persName>Mr H</persName> will I
                presume be glad<lb/> to furnish.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">At the same time I hope that I do not trespass so far<lb/> on your
                patience gentlemen for saying that I trust that no<lb/> intention is entertained of
                setting aside the <persName>Rev. Mr Gotthelf</persName><lb/> in favor of a new
                comer, unless there exist some urgent reasons for<lb/> his dismissal of which I have
                not heard. As respects <persName>Mr<lb/> Henry</persName> I confess that I am not
                favorably impressed of him,<lb/> owing to his being instrumental in <persName>Mr
                    Gutheim</persName> being deprived<lb/> of his office, though he has some better
                one than he had before;<lb/> and that <persName>Mr Henry</persName> had no right to
                refer to me at all, as we exchan-<lb/>ged but one letter, and never had any
                intercourse whatever before his<lb/> quitting <placeName>Europe</placeName> and
                since his arrival here. Of course I have<lb/> no personal ill-will to him; but I do
                not approve of any one trying</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to obtain the situation of another especially when he has a position which<lb/>
                secures him a living. But as you do not ask my opinion to govern you<lb/> in your
                choice, I have to repeat that I <del>?</del> refer you to those<lb/> having the
                information desired to enable you to come to a correct<lb/> judgment.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is my sincere hope that you may resolve<lb/> on the best method
                to promote the interest of our Religion, and<lb/> that peace &amp; good will may
                reside among you. I need not add<lb/> that I shall be happy to be of any service in
                my power to your<lb/> congregation &amp; you individually for the kind consideration
                manifested<lb/> towards me and my public labours.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Wishing you <add>Hebrew</add> and that your prayers may<lb/> be
                answered.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Resp your obt servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
